                    class="bi bi-chevron-up icon-close"></i></div>
                <div id="faq2" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                  <p>
                    It is necessary to apply a generous amount over the body 15 minutes before exposure to the sun. Then
                    repeat the process every two hours.

                  </p>
                </div>
              </li>

              <li>
                <div data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#faq3" class="collapsed question">What is the country of origin for
                  Momento products? <i class="bi bi-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i
                    class="bi bi-chevron-up icon-close"></i></div>
                <div id="faq3" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                  <p>
                    An Egyptian brand with ingredients from United Kingdom.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </li>

              <li>
                <div data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#faq4" class="collapsed question">Are the products suitable for
                  children?<i class="bi bi-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bi bi-chevron-up icon-close"></i></div>
                <div id="faq4" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                  <p>
                    Yes, they are suitable for children above 3 years.

                  </p>
                </div>
              </li>

              <li>
                <div data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#faq5" class="collapsed question">What are the differences between
                  protection SPF? <i class="bi bi-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i
                    class="bi bi-chevron-up icon-close"></i></div>
                <div id="faq5" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                  <p>
                    It depends on the skin tone, so we advise those of fair/light skin tone to choose the hightest
                    possible SPF.
                </div>
              </li>

              <li>
                <div data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#faq6" class="collapsed question">What are the benefits of after
                  sun gel? <i class="bi bi-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bi bi-chevron-up icon-close"></i></div>
                <div id="faq6" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                  <p>
                    The sun's rays raises the temperature of your body, so you can use the gel that cools and
                    moisturizes the inflamed areas and it would refresh your body.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </li>

              <li>
                <div data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#faq7" class="collapsed question">Should we use the sunscreen
